Upload Document

 

To upload a Document:

1. Click the Create / Upload button or when in the Cultural Objects click on the Create Document button
Note: Have in mind that if the second option is used the next two points will be preset and can't be changed

 

2. Select the Upload option

3. Select the context you want the Document to be created

Note: You can create the Document in the context of a cultural object or in the context of project or any conservation activity. Creating Document in the context of another system objects means that this Document will be part of that context and the permissions on that Document will depend on this context.

4. Select "Select file.." option and chose the file from you local drive.

"Document" as a type will be recognized automatically if you are uploading word, excel, etc. files.

5. Select the sub-type of the document

6. Fill mandatory Document data 

The mandatory fields depends on the type of the document you want to be uploaded. 

Fields can appear as mandatory depending on the selected type.

 

 

7.  Select Upload

Uploaded Documents

The first tab of the document presents its content.
